comments.comment:
It looks like node1 is streaming wrong part of SSTable file.
With key cache turned on, this may relate to CASSANDRA-4687.
can not reproduce with keycache turned off on node1
i think i just reproduced this with key cache turned off..
confirmed that I have seen this with key_cache_size_in_mb: 0 for every node in the cluster

We just migrated our cluster to 1.2 here and we're having a similar issue when running repairs. Since the call stack mentioned "CompressedFileStreamTask" we tried to disable the column family compaction and scrub it. The following repairs worked fine so we decided to re-enable the compression, which made the error come back.
I don't know if it was a coincidence or if there is an issue with the compression, can anyone else reproduce the behavior?
Does that help narrow it down, Yuki?

Update: We moved back the failing CF to sstable_compression='' and it doesn't show errors in the log anymore.
The other CFs are working/repairing fine, but nodetool netstats during a repair shows wrong percentages (156098%...) could it be related?

I'd be happy to run other tests if it can help finding the issue.

alprema wrong percentage was fixed in CASSANDRA-5130 and will be released in 1.2.1.

I'm trying to reproduce myself but still no luck. Some logs before error happend may help if you can upload.

yukim Great for the percentages, I'm relieved my other CFs are not impacted by the issue.
For the main problem at hand here are a couple logs (We have a 3 nodes cluster and the problem occurred between 01 and 02, we can see that 02 throws an exception when receiving the stream, which causes a Broken Pipe exception on the 01 side).

I'm seeing what looks like the same error every time I try and add a new node to my cluster.

i'm wondering if the DecoratedKey RuntimeException is a manifestation but not the real issue here.

After unrelated IOExceptions during the repair while bootstrapping a new node, it appears that the IOException/broken pipe was thrown.

maybe when we retry it starts streaming from the wrong location in the sstable after attempting to recover from the original IOException?

I found one problem that can send extra chunk to destination which causes reading from wrong position.
This happens when the streaming section of sstable falls into the edge of compression chunks.
Test and fix attached.
+1 patch looks good. verified as fixed.

Switched to 1.2.2 and re-enabled compression, repair now works like a charm.
Thanks.
